  "prompt": "What are the 3 best things you would recommend to improve your questions on Quora?",
  "response": "Improving your questions on Quora can enhance the quality of answers you receive and engage a broader audience. Here are three recommendations:\n\n1. **Be Specific and Clear**: Formulate your question to be as specific as possible. Instead of asking vague questions, provide context and detail about what you're looking for. For example, instead of asking, \"What are tips for studying?\" you could ask, \"What are effective study techniques for retaining information in college-level biology courses?\" This clarity helps potential responders understand exactly what you're seeking.\n\n2. **Include Relevant Context**: Share any necessary background information that may help others provide better answers. This could include personal experiences, why you're asking the question, or what you\u2019ve already considered. For example, if you're asking for advice on job interviews, mention the specific industry and any challenges you're facing. This allows responders to tailor their answers to your situation.\n\n3. **Engage with the Community**: Before posting, take a moment to review existing answers or similar questions on the platform. This not only helps you refine your question but also shows you\u2019re engaged with the community and can lead to follow-up questions or discussions. You might also mention what aspects of existing answers were helpful or unhelpful for you, encouraging more targeted responses. \n\nBy following these tips, you'll likely get richer, more useful answers on Quora.",
